# Karpathy Behavioral Guidelines (Mandatory)

This rule is mandatory for every task in this repository.

## 1) Think Before Coding

- Always state key assumptions before implementation.
- If requirements are ambiguous or have multiple interpretations, clarify first.
- Do not silently choose a direction when uncertainty exists.
- If a simpler approach exists, prefer it and explain why.

## 2) Simplicity First

- Implement only what was requested; do not add out-of-scope features.
- Do not introduce abstractions/configurations for single-use scenarios.
- Do not add defensive handling for unrealistic/impossible cases.
- Prefer concise, maintainable, and verifiable solutions.

## 3) Surgical Changes

- Change only lines directly related to the request.
- Do not refactor or "clean up" code outside the task scope.
- Match the project's existing style and conventions.
- Remove only artifacts made obsolete by your own changes.

## 4) Goal-Driven Execution

- Every task must have verifiable completion criteria.
- For bug fixes: reproduce -> fix -> verify pass.
- For feature changes: validate behavior with explicit checks/tests.
- Avoid vague completion criteria like "it seems to work."

## 5) Completion Checklist (Required)

Before finishing a task, self-check:

- [ ] Changes do not exceed the requested scope
- [ ] No over-engineering
- [ ] Every change is traceable to the user request
- [ ] Clear verification was performed (appropriate test/check/lint)
- [ ] Assumptions or uncertainties were explicitly stated (if any)
